# cchook-recovery: leak tokens (one token per line)
#
# When a tool_use turn is dropped as malformed, a stray lone token often leaks into the
# visible text. If the last assistant message contains any of these tokens on a line by
# itself (surrounding whitespace allowed, case-insensitive), the hook nudges Claude to
# continue. Tokens are matched literally (regex metacharacters are NOT interpreted).
#
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored. Add new tokens as you observe them.
# If this file is missing or empty, the hook falls back to the built-in defaults below.
court
county
course
cource
call
